@startuml
title Text and Font - Practical Flow

skinparam ParticipantPadding 8

actor "User code" as User
participant "Font" as Font
participant "Glyph atlas" as Atlas
participant "Texture" as Texture
participant "TextRenderCommand" as TextCommand
participant "RenderContext" as RenderContext

User -> Font : load font file
Font -> Font : rasterize requested glyphs
Font -> Atlas : place glyph pixels
Atlas -> Texture : upload atlas image

User -> TextCommand : create text command
TextCommand -> Font : request glyph metrics and atlas areas
TextCommand -> TextCommand : build quads with alignment
TextCommand -> RenderContext : execute()
RenderContext -> Texture : bind atlas
RenderContext -> RenderContext : draw text mesh

note bottom
Text drawing is regular rendering: font data creates
an atlas texture, then text commands draw textured quads.
end note

@enduml
